Definition.WordDefinition:
Clinton \Clin"ton\ 1. William Jefferson Clinton, b. 1946. The 42d president of the United States, from 1993-. Also known as {Bill Clinton}. [Prop.] [PJC]
2. Hillary Rodham Clinton, b. 1947. Attorney and wife of Bill Clinton, the 42d president of the United States. [Prop.] [PJC]

Clinton n 1: 42nd President of the United States (1946-) [syn: {Bill Clinton}, {William Jefferson Clinton}, {President Clinton}] 2: United States politician who as governor of New York supported the project to build the Erie Canal (1769-1828) [syn: {DeWitt Clinton}] 3: a town in east central Iowa
